# Personio API v2 OAuth2 client credentials.
# Create an API credential in Personio (Settings > Integrations > API credentials)
# and copy the client id / secret here. NEVER commit the filled-in .env file.
PERSONIO_CLIENT_ID=papi-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
PERSONIO_CLIENT_SECRET=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Optional: override the API base URL (defaults to https://api.personio.de).
# PERSONIO_BASE_URL=https://api.personio.de

# Optional: steady-state floor (ms) for the request throttle. The client already
# paces each endpoint to the refill rate Personio reports in its x-ratelimit-*
# headers, so this is usually unnecessary. Set a positive value only to throttle
# more conservatively than the server requires. Default: 0 (pace from headers).
# PERSONIO_MIN_REQUEST_INTERVAL_MS=0

# Optional: space-separated OAuth2 scopes to request. When omitted, Personio
# grants all scopes available to the credential. Document the scopes your
# credential needs, e.g.:
#   personio:attendances:read personio:absences:read personio:persons:read
# PERSONIO_SCOPES=personio:attendances:read personio:absences:read

# The two account-config values below can alternatively (and preferably) live in
# personio.config.json and be passed to the examples via --config; the config
# file takes precedence over these env vars. See personio.config.example.json.

# Optional: Custom Report ids used by the ReportSource. Attendance and absences
# come from different Custom Reports, so each record type has its own id; when a
# type's id is set, the examples default that type to the report-based source
# instead of the granular API. Set only the ones you use.
# PERSONIO_ATTENDANCE_REPORT_ID=00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
# PERSONIO_ABSENCE_REPORT_ID=00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

# Optional: your account's personnel-number ("Kostenträger Nummer") custom-field
# id(s), comma-separated (first match wins). It is a custom /v2/persons attribute
# with an opaque, account-specific id and no human label, so the API source can
# only resolve it by id. Find yours with `scripts/probe-scopes.ts` / a persons
# read. When unset, the library's generic fallback keys apply.
# PERSONIO_PERSONNEL_FIELD_IDS=dynamic_1234567890abcd.12345678
